   "body" : "The commands `getpeerinfo` and `getnetworkinfo` returns the services a node provides in the form of a flag (in the field `services`). This PR adds a field `servicesnames` (resp. `localservicesnames`) which contains the names of these services so that a user does not have to parse the flag to know which services his node provides.\r\n\r\nFrom :\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"version\": 179900,\r\n  \"subversion\": \"/Satoshi:0.17.99/\",\r\n  \"protocolversion\": 70015,\r\n  \"localservices\": \"000000000000040d\",\r\n  \"localrelay\": true,\r\n  ...\r\n```\r\nTo :\r\n```\r\nbitcoin-cli getnetworkinfo\r\n{\r\n  \"version\": 179900,\r\n  \"subversion\": \"/Satoshi:0.17.99/\",\r\n  \"protocolversion\": 70015,\r\n  \"localservices\": [\r\n    \"NODE_NETWORK\",\r\n    \"NODE_BLOOM\",\r\n    \"NODE_WITNESS\",\r\n    \"NODE_NETWORK_LIMITED\"\r\n  ],\r\n  \"localrelay\": true,\r\n   ...\r\n```",
